## Plan (.2 per-run replay->record->pairwise-eval pipeline)

**Scope:** Library-only in internal/bench. NO CLI (.4), NO cohort selection
(.1 done, consumed), NO caching (.3). Consumes bench.CohortRun from cohort.go.

### Recorder extraction — DECISION: option (a), in THIS bead, partially closing etude-0rt
recordRun/allocateReplayRunID/sourceInputRefs are UNEXPORTED on the cli
replayRunner type (replay.go:236/333/323); bench lives in internal/bench and
cannot reach them. Reimplementing (option b) would copy-paste the gated
files-map/Skill<->Producer-mirror/replay_of/run-id-allocation dance that
etude-0rt explicitly flags as a repeated correctness hazard. EXTRACT to an
exported helper in internal/replay (no import cycle: replay already imports
artifactstore/refstore/runmanifest; cli+bench both import replay):

  // internal/replay/record.go (NEW)
  type RunRecorder struct { Store refstore.Store; Now func() time.Time }
  func (r RunRecorder) Record(ctx, resolved ResolvedStage, res RunResult,
        sourceRunID, sourceStageName string) (RecordedRun, error)
  type RecordedRun struct { RunID, Commit, OutputArtifact, OutputPath string }

Record does exactly what recordRun does today: AddContent(output)->files map;
copy each source input raw via store.ReadCommitFile(resolved.Commit, path);
Stage{ProducedBy:"replay", GitSHA:resolved.GitSHA, Skill:res.Producer.Skill,
Producer:res.Producer, Inputs:sourceInputRefs, Output:ArtifactFromManifestArtifact,
ReplayOf:&ReplayLink{sourceRunID,sourceStageName,resolved.Commit}}; manifest from
resolved.Workflow/WorkflowVersion/Refs; Writer.Write. allocateReplayRunID +
sourceInputRefs move into replay too (exported AllocateRunID or kept as Record
internals). RecordedRun.OutputArtifact = outputArtifact.SHA256 (the pin bench needs).
Move allocateReplayRunID -> replay; eval.AllocateEvalID stays (its own ns).

REFACTOR cli/replay.go: recordRun becomes a thin wrapper calling
RunRecorder{Store:store, Now:r.now}.Record(...) then printing the existing
"recorded replay run %s (commit %s)" line. Behavior MUST be byte-identical;
existing replay_test.go stays green (this is the regression gate). This only
PARTIALLY satisfies etude-0rt (replay path only; capture.go append-path
refactor stays open) — note that in 0rt, do NOT close it.

### Pipeline API (Q1) — consumable by .4
  // internal/bench/run.go (NEW)
  type Pipeline struct {
      Store    refstore.Store
      Runner   replay.Runner   // injected; StubRunner in tests
      Judge    eval.Judge      // injected; StubJudge in tests
