  }
root is passed in (repoRoot is a cli helper; .4 resolves it) so bench stays
TTY-free. A cohort-level loop helper is deferred to .4 (it owns abort/skip UX).

### Per-run flow (Q2) — precise
1. resolved, err := replay.ResolveInputs(ctx, p.Store, cr.RunID, cr.Stage.Name).
2. Materialize inputs via inp.ReadContent (mirror replay.go:159-173;
   ErrPointerNotMaterialized -> error, though .1 already filtered pointers).
3. Read ORIGINAL output bytes: store.ReadCommitFile(ctx, resolved.Commit,
   resolved.Output.Path) (resolve exposes ReadContent for INPUTS only; output
   read is separate). Its SHA256 is resolved.Output.Artifact (no recompute).
4. worktree.Checkout(ctx, root, resolved.GitSHA); defer Close. Build producer by
   merging resolved.Producer with p.Overrides (mergeString pattern, replay.go:177).
5. res := p.Runner.Run(RunRequest{WorktreeDir, ScratchDir(MkdirTemp), Inputs,
   OutputRole/MediaType from resolved.Output, Producer}). Empty output -> error.
6. rec := p.Recorder.Record(...) -> mints ReplayRunID + Commit + OutputArtifact sha.
7. Build pairwise EvalRequest{Method:"pairwise", Targets:[A,B], Producer:judge id}:
   A = EvalInput{Role:"original", MediaType:resolved.Output.MediaType,
       Content:<orig bytes>, Source:ArtifactSource{RunID:cr.RunID,
       Stage:cr.Stage.Name, Commit:resolved.Commit, Artifact:resolved.Output.Artifact}}
   B = EvalInput{Role:"replay", MediaType:res.MediaType, Content:res.Output,
       Source:ArtifactSource{RunID:rec.RunID, Stage:cr.Stage.Name,
       Commit:rec.Commit, Artifact:rec.OutputArtifact}}
   Both commit+sha256 pinned -> EvalResult.Validate passes.
8. ev := (&eval.PairwiseEvaluator{Judge:p.Judge, Seed:p.Seed}).Evaluate(ctx,req).
9. Build EvalResult{EvalResultVersion:1, EvalID:AllocateEvalID(base=EvalIDBase
   "pairwise",cr.RunID,cr.Stage.Name,now), Method:"pairwise", Score:ev.Score,
   Findings:ev.Findings, Targets:[A.Source,B.Source], Producer, Created:now}.

### Persistence boundary (Q2 cont) — .2 PERSISTS
.2 writes the EvalResult via eval.Writer.Write (refs/etude/evals/<id>) and returns
it in BenchOutcome. Rationale: recording the replay is what pins B, and .3 cache
keys off persisted EvalResults — so the durable doc must exist now. .3 adds a
pre-judge lookup seam (BenchRun gets a cache hook later); .2 ships the always-
evaluate-and-persist path. .4 consumes BenchOutcome for aggregation/report.

### Producer overrides (Q4 axis)
  type ProducerOverrides struct { SkillID,SkillRepo,SkillVersion,Model,Harness,
      HarnessVersion string + matching *Changed bools }
Mirror replayProducerFlags merge (replay.go:177-188) inside BenchRun so the
replay runs a NEW skill-version/model vs the original recorded producer — the
comparison axis. ExecRunner echoes/overrides via RunResult.Producer; recorder
persists res.Producer. (.4 maps CLI flags onto this struct.)

### Errors (Q5)
BenchRun returns (BenchOutcome{}, err) on ANY per-run failure (resolve, pointer,
checkout, runner, empty output, record, evaluate, judge, validate, write). It
does NOT decide abort-vs-skip — that's .4's cohort loop. Wrap with run-id context
("bench run %s stage %s: %w").

